# UDS Token Architecture

This rule preserves the token structure that is already correct on the doc site. Agents must not rediscover or redesign token architecture during an import.

## Primary source

The primary token source is the **Variables tab** in the UDS Tokens Figma file:

- Figma file key: `iqKgR73ubUHpQTIcF7XGMy`
- Figma file: **UDS Tokens**

Agents MUST attempt to read Figma Variables directly before requesting exported ZIPs.

ZIP exports are fallback only when direct variable access is unavailable, incomplete, or cannot produce a deterministic normalized token model.

## CSS outputs are final

The current doc-site token output structure is canonical:

- `_uds-primitive` -> `uds-docs/uds/tokens/primitives.css`
- `uds-color` -> `uds-docs/uds/tokens/semantic.css`
- `uds-font` -> `uds-docs/uds/tokens/semantic.css`
- `uds-font-scale` -> `uds-docs/uds/tokens/semantic.css`
- `uds-space` -> `uds-docs/uds/tokens/semantic.css`
- `uds-border` -> `uds-docs/uds/tokens/semantic.css`
- Figma text styles / text composites -> `uds-docs/uds/tokens/text-styles.css`

Do not create extra token CSS files without explicit user instruction.

## Figma collections

### Imported collections

These collections are expected and imported:

| Collection | Expected role | CSS output |
|---|---|---|
| `_uds-primitive` | Raw palette / numeric / font primitives | `primitives.css` |
| `uds-color` | Semantic color tokens across themes | `semantic.css` |
| `uds-font` | Font family / font token modes | `semantic.css` |
| `uds-font-scale` | Type scale modes | `semantic.css` |
| `uds-space` | Spacing / density modes | `semantic.css` |
| `uds-border` | Border radius and width tokens | `semantic.css` |

### Known non-imported / deferred collections

These collections may exist in Figma and MUST be reported, but are not generated into CSS today unless the user explicitly asks to add support:

| Collection | Current treatment |
|---|---|
| `uds-elevation` | Deferred / currently not imported |
| `uds-motion` | Deferred / currently not imported |
| `uds-style-icon` | Known non-imported collection |
| `uds-rules` | Known non-imported collection |

Non-imported collections are not errors. They become errors only if the user asks to import them and no CSS contract exists.

## Expected modes

### `_uds-primitive`

Expected single mode:

- `primitive value`

### `uds-color`

Expected theme modes:

- `base (light)`
- `base (dark)`
- `resman (light)`
- `resman (dark)`
- `anyonehome (light)`
- `inhabit (light)`

Mode-to-selector mapping:

| Figma mode | CSS selector |
|---|---|
| `base (light)` | `:root` default |
| `base (dark)` | `[data-color-scheme="dark"]` |
| `resman (light)` | `[data-theme="resman"]` |
| `resman (dark)` | `[data-theme="resman"][data-color-scheme="dark"]` |
| `anyonehome (light)` | `[data-theme="anyonehome"]` |
| `inhabit (light)` | `[data-theme="inhabit"]` |

### `uds-font`

Expected font modes should map to:

- default Inter in `:root`
- `[data-font="poppins"]`
- `[data-font="roboto"]`
- `[data-font="lexend"]`

### `uds-font-scale`

Expected scale modes should map to:

- default in `:root`
- `[data-font-scale="smaller"]`
- `[data-font-scale="larger"]`

### `uds-space`

Expected density modes should map to:

- default in `:root`
- `[data-density="comfortable"]`

### `uds-border`

Border tokens are semantic tokens in `semantic.css`. If modes exist, they must be reported and mapped explicitly before generation.

## Naming transforms

### Primitive variables

Figma:

```text
_uds-primitive / color / slate / 60-M
```

CSS:

```css
--uds-primitive-color-slate-60-M
```

Rule:

```text
_uds-primitive / <path...> -> --uds-primitive-<path-joined-with-hyphen>
```

### Semantic color variables

Figma:

```text
uds / color / surface / interactive-default
```

CSS:

```css
--uds-color-surface-interactive-default
```

Rule:

```text
uds / color / <category> / <name> -> --uds-color-<category>-<name>
```

### Other semantic variables

Use the same prefix pattern:

- `uds / font / ...` -> `--uds-font-...`
- `uds / font-scale / ...` -> `--uds-font-scale-...`
- `uds / space / ...` -> `--uds-space-...`
- `uds / border / ...` -> `--uds-border-...`

## Layering rules

- Primitive tokens store raw values.
- Semantic tokens should preserve aliases to primitives where possible.
- Component CSS consumes semantic tokens, not primitives.
- Font tokens may alias font-scale tokens and primitive font family / weight tokens.
- Text style classes in `text-styles.css` consume semantic font tokens.

Do not flatten semantic aliases to raw hex/px values unless direct Figma data cannot expose aliases and the user approves fallback generation.

## Don't claim a token is missing — verify first

Before telling a user, or writing into a report, that a token doesn't
exist, CHECK. Read `uds-docs/uds/tokens/semantic.css` / `primitives.css`,
or run `search_design_system` against the UDS Tokens library. Asserting
absence from memory is a recurring error — the 2px focus-gap token was
twice reported as "missing" when `--uds-space-025` (2px) was in
`semantic.css` the whole time.

For reference, the default-mode spacing scale in `semantic.css` is
continuous and finer than people remember:

`space-0` (0) · `space-025` (2px) · `space-050` (4px) · `space-075`
(6px) · `space-100` (8px) · `space-125` (10px) · `space-150` (12px) ·
`space-175` (14px) · `space-200` (16px) · `space-250` (20px) · `space-300`
(24px) · … continuing in 4px-ish steps up to `space-1250` (100px). So a
2px gap binds to `space-025`, a 6px gap to `space-075`, and so on. The
`[data-density="comfortable"]` mode re-maps these (e.g. `space-025`
resolves to 6px there) — so bind the variable, never the resolved px.

This applies to every token family, not just spacing: verify color,
radius, and effect-style names against the tokens CSS / library before
declaring a gap.

## Don't claim a token value (or a "drift") — resolve it first

A rendered size is not a token value. Before stating what a token
resolves to — or reporting that Figma and code "disagree" — resolve the
variable properly:

1. **Follow the alias chain to a concrete number.** A semantic
   font-size or space token aliases through collections
   (`uds-font` → `uds-font-scale` → `_uds-primitive`) before it lands on
   a literal. Walk it with `getVariableByIdAsync` until you hit a number
   — don't infer the value from a node's rendered `fontSize` or from a
   screenshot.
2. **Enumerate the modes.** Type sizes route through `uds-font-scale`
   (`larger` / `default` / `smaller`) and spacing through `uds-space`
   density (`comfortable`). One token has several values. Report the
   **default**-mode value as the baseline, and name the other modes only
   if they matter — never quote one mode as "the" value.
3. **Code CSS is downstream, not the source.** `uds/tokens/*.css` is
   generated from Figma and can carry a single non-default scale baked
   in. It currently ships the *larger*-scale type values
   (`font-size-base` 16, `font-size-xs` 12, `label/base-medium` 16) while
   Figma's default scale is 14 / 10 / 14. Never lift a px from the code
   CSS to "correct" Figma — Figma's default scale is the source;
   reconcile the other direction via `import-figma-tokens`.

This is the value-side partner of "Don't claim a token is missing." The
helper-text "10 vs 12" investigation flip-flopped twice because the value
was inferred from a rendered size instead of resolved through the
font-scale modes — default `xs` is 10px, `larger` 12px, `smaller` 8px.

## Architecture validation gate

Before importing tokens, `figma-token-audit` MUST report:

- Direct Figma Variables read: success / partial / failed
- Imported collections present/missing
- Non-imported collections present and counts
- Mode names per imported collection
- Token counts per imported collection
- Alias graph validity
- Generated CSS names that would differ from current CSS
- Structure diff before value diff
- Confidence and breaking-change classification

If the Figma Variables structure cannot be read or does not match this contract, fail closed and report. Do not generate CSS.
